{
  "stem": "13382.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on the street, they used to sort of ambush Jewish children and stones-- throwing stone.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never had anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, I can't remember that any of this experience.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I always--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- not direct anti-Semitism from them to me personally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Somehow-- I don't know what it meant, because people draw to me, and I draw to other people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I sort of-- I looked everyone into their-- you see, the biggest danger is when you are afraid.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was never afraid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When I saw someone coming, I gave him a nod, rather.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How are you-- you know, that sort of a attitude.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and this way, I-- I never experienced really face to face a sort of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It happened once.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A very good friend of mine-- he's gentile.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used to go and play to his house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was Slovakian, or Czech, or something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a-- the-- his father was an official at the railways.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the mother called the son in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I overheard, telling him in Czech, she said, why do you play with that circumcised?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I understood what it meant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was in shock.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went home, and I went, mother, how is it possible?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What's wrong with me?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So mother said, that's the life, darling.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, you have to get used to it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Not everybody likes Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But that was the only practically sort of experience, which I experienced.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it wasn't even really said into my face.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, those people-- not so much who are fitted in into the society, right-- payots and this-- you know, when you didn't have-- I mean, people didn't even really know on the street, unless they know that you are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
